items.name: Penis covered eyes
items.description:
Introduction

This is a LyCORIS to enhance the concept of "penis_covered_eyes". I think the name speaks for itself.

Notice: it has only some fixed positions to choose. See the examples. Using other position tags may lead to weird results.

How to use

I recommand using it in weight 0.7-0.8. Higher weight may give you overbaked results

Training details:

Traingset is of 43 images. They are mirrored before training. Half of them are chosen as regularization images. Total steps are about 4300.

Regularization = true

resolution=768

batch_size=2

epoch=10

network_dim=32

network_alpha=32

clip_skip=2

Using AdamW8bits as optimizer:

  • lr="1e-4"

  • unet_lr="1e-4"

  • text_encoder_lr="1e-5"

Locon parameters:

  • conv_dim=4

  • conv_alpha=4

items.name: Emilia Clarke [Embedding]
items.description:
The very first embedding I created with some moderate success. I'm aware there's an entire checkpoint model out there for recreating her likeness and compared to that, an embedding is somewhat limited. Still, I have managed to create good images using this embedding and I hope you can do so as well.

As usual, this embedding has been trained on SD 1.5 and works well on most 1.5 based models. I've run into issues using the embedding with certain models such as RealisticVision 1.3. Lowering the embedding weight or using inpainting to re-generate the face really helps here.

If you enjoy my creations and want to support me or have a face you'd like to commission, consider supporting me on Ko-Fi or Buy Me A Coffee :)

items.name: Houseki no Kuni (Land of the Lustrous)
Cameron Diaz
items.description:
A TI of the little-known, obscure American actress Cameron Diaz.

Works very well at Strength 1. Given Ms. Diaz's propensity to wear thin clothing with no bra there were a lot of 'pokies' in the training data, so negative prompting may be required to remove.

Also, her heyday was the mid-to-late 90's when 512x512 images were "High Res", so many of the training images are from her later years. Despite this it seems to work well, especially if adding an approximate age you want her to look.

items.name: Azumi by koyama yuu japanese manga ninja girl
items.description:
Japanese explanation is below

日本語説明はしたにあります↓

  • This Lora&locon model is LoRA&locon, a character named Azumi, the main character in a Japanese manga called Azumi.

  • Please note that the locon extension is required to use this model.

  • The trigger word is azumichan1.

  • The basic clothing and hairstyle prompts are

    purple japanese clothes,blue eyes,sleeveless,high ponytail.

  • Basically, the Nai series models work.

    The 7th anime models are particularly compatible, but even if they contain realistic elements such as AOM models, they can be made to resemble them to some extent.

  • For those of you who don't know this character, here's a brief description of her is Ninja & Assassin & Saint & Innocent & Beautiful Girl & Absolute Virgin.

  • You can optionally use cape,katana, or kimono, to recreate the original.

If you set "japanese clothes" and "kimono" as a negative prompt, it will be easier to dress the doll in other clothes.

Thanks to the author for making the cutest little girl.

日本語説明

  • このLora&loconモデルは日本の漫画のあずみという漫画の主人公のあずみというキャラのLoRA&loconです。

  • 使用時にはloconの拡張機能が必要なので注意してください。

  • トリガーワードは azumichan1 です。

  • 基本的な服装・髪型のプロンプトはpurple japanese clothes, blue eyes,sleeveless,high ponytailになります。

  • オプションでcape,kimono,katanaなどで原作の再現もできます。

  • ネガティブプロンプトにjapanese clothes,kimonoなどを入れると他の服を着せやすくなります。

  • 基本的にNai系列のモデルでは動作します。

    特に相性がいいのは7th animeモデルですがAOMモデルなどのリアル要素が入っていてもある程度似せれます。

  • このキャラクターを知らない方に短い文でキャラの説明をすると忍者＆アサシン＆聖女＆天真爛漫＆美少女＆絶対的処女です。

  • 最高に可愛い少女を作ってくれた作者に感謝します。

items.description:
This is a custom LoRA model for the character Frisk from the popular video game Undertale. I trained the model using 84 high-quality images and utilized the AbyssOrangeMix3 model.

For optimal results, I recommend using the Euler a sampler, with the following recommended parameters:

  • CFG scale of 7

  • 20 steps

  • hires upscaler set to Latent (nearest-exact)

  • 20 hires steps

  • Denoising strength of 0.52

For optimal performance, it is recommended that the weight of the LoRA be set within the range of 0.6-0.8.

To accurately depict Frisk's appearance, I suggest including yellow skin, closed eyes, and expressionless in the positive prompt. Additionally, to ensure the correct number of stripes on Frisk's shirt, I recommend placing two two stripes or two purple stripes in the positive prompt and three stripes in the negative prompt.

It should be noted that this model has a tendency to add vignetting in the corners of the output image. To mitigate this, I suggest including vignetting in the negative prompt.

Please feel free to leave a comment below if you have any requests for LoRA models.

items.name: Danica Rockwood
items.description:
Famous and talented cosplayer Danica Rockwood. She does a wide range of styles for her cosplay and modeling so I thought it would be neat to have her be able to work with some stable diffusions.

Tested with a good number of models with fairly consistent results at getting an accurate (but not always perfect) representation. Tested on mostly realistic styled models, but it may work on some anime ones too.

Please let me know what you think and if there's any errors you see, it will help me learn and improve if it needs any fixes.

Trained at 5000 steps with a variable learning rate. Tested lesser steps and they all looked decent, but figured I'd keep the 5000 one.

I am semi new with creating Textual Inversions, but I do think the result here is good. I was aiming for versatility so this is trained on 1.5, as I heard that's the best way to get your TIs to work with a wide range of models.

All of the outputs were with Restore Faces enabled. I did have some okay results with it off with some early tests, but I enabled it at a certain point and forgot to alternate.

I used a range of 5-12 CFG for testing, it started to get a decent representation around 9-10, but it didn't look awful at around 7.

items.name: H.R. Giger Arh+
items.description:
H.R. Giger Arh+

[EDIT: Retrained and overhauled version 10.0 is up and should now work with most models and LoRAs out there.]

This LoRA model might work or it might not. I did this mainly for my own enjoyment as I wanted a model that specifically does high quality replication of the organic patterns in Giger's airbrush works. I went through my library and scanned in the highest quality images I had, some of them were digital photographs of the real works, so the source material was really high quality for the most part. When it works, it creates reaaally smooth and wide dynamic range renders.

But, as this was my very first time training anything, I probably messed something up as when the LoRA training rendered out test prompts, the images were 100% what I was aiming for - but when I tested the LoRA out on Automatic1111's WebUI, nothing seemed to work or give the wide contrast results - it's probably something in my settings or the implementation of the LoRA network models is not quite there yet. At some point, like magic, it just started working more and more.

Anyhoo, on WebUI, the best results come from somewhat lower CFG range, like 3-5 and with a base model that gives interesting stuff to paint on. I'll dive deeper into the training stuff and was thinking of making a SDv2 model with 768 sample images, but this seems to work ok so far. Test it out and show me what you create with it.

H.R. Giger (1940-2014)

modelVersions.name: v10.0
modelVersions.description: Turns out that training with specific version of XFormers, you get a LoRA that doesn't activate or activates at random, which is why previous versions were a bit iffy. Now with a new card (3060, 12GB) and a polished set of sample images, I managed to train a LoRA that passes all (at least on my end) tests. Trained with 65 images at 1024px so it might produce weird stuff with resolutions below 768.

modelVersions.name: v3
modelVersions.description:
This one's a BigBoi™. Trained at whopping 1024px using same size sample images, it can create some pretty mad details. Best suited for img2img (which I intended this for) but works really well with various checkpoints (be sure to try this with the Giger checkpoint by Mince >> https://civitai.com/models/12124/hans-rudi-giger-style).

Best is to render at 1024 x 1024 but it can stretch over it. I've been doing test renders at 896 x 1280 and results have been pretty amazing so far. Of course, best case scenario would be to have a checkpoint model underneath that is trained in 1024 from the get-go, but still, this was just a funny science experiment. I'm really tempted to try 1280 training, just for shts n giggles. But this one is already giving loads of details.

modelVersions.name: v2
modelVersions.description: More carefully curated sample images, only the best quality were selected and the whole batch was prepared and trained at 768px. Might have to do it again as one of the Li paintings became VERY prominent and dominates any portrait where you specify "woman" as a token. But the model really shines when used with img2img, I've had some incredible results with it.

  • New plugsuit from Rebuild 3.0 - souryuu asuka langley, interface headset, multicolored bodysuit, eyepatch. Adding red plugsuit to negatives sumewhat helps.

items.name: haru urara (umamusume)
items.description:
Update:I have remade the model of LoCon, and compared to the previous LoHa version, the fit is now higher.

Note:

This is a LYCORIS model, and you need to install a1111-sd-webui-locon extension to use this model.

And I have some advice for those who want to train LYCORIS models: if you want to train characters, I do not recommend using LoHa, and instead recommend using LoCon. I have been testing the LoHa model with different hyperparameters over the past few days, but recently the author of LYCORIS suggested that LoCon is better for training characters. This confirms my suspicion that LoHa is too prone to overfitting when it comes to training characters. So in order to avoid this problem, the previous LoHa version was underfitting as a result.

Therefore, I do not recommend downloading the old version

Trigger word:

haru urara

Suggest prompt

Race clothes:

haru urara,jacket, gym uniform, shirt,red buruma,hair bow,

And optional.

bandaid on leg, fingerless gloves,

Adjust the tag weights appropriately.

casual:

haru urara,overalls,overall shorts,pink shirt,hair bow

tracen school uniform

haru urara,tracen school uniform,white thighhighs,bowtie,hair bow

I'm sorry.'flower-shaped pupils' is not work.

The new recommended prompts are not applicable to the old version, and the old version only serves as a failed example.
